This paper discusses the investigation of cloud storage services from a security and forensics perspective, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of different operating systems and web browsers, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the retrieval of artifacts, which could fall under cybercrime (cs.CY) or digital libraries (cs.DL).
